---
<BaseLayout
  title="About RRM Academy | Restorative Reproductive Medicine"
  description={`Expert-led education in restorative reproductive medicine. 12 clinician-taught courses and ${libraryCount} research resources, all free or low-cost.`}
  canonicalUrl="https://rrmacademy.org/about"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  speakable={['.about-hero p', '.about-lead', '.about-mission']}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h1 class="hero-title animate-enter" style="--stagger: 0;">About RRM Academy</h1>
      <p class="about-hero__tagline animate-enter" style="--stagger: 1;">Education for true healing and reproductive health</p>
      <p class="about-hero__updated animate-enter" style="--stagger: 2;"><LastUpdated path="/about/" /></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="page-body">
  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <p class="about-lead">
        RRM Academy provides expert-led, evidence-based education in Restorative Reproductive Medicine (RRM) for patients and healthcare professionals. Through 12 online courses and a <a href="/library/">research library</a> of {libraryCount} publications, we equip individuals and clinicians with the knowledge to find and treat the root causes of conditions like endometriosis, PCOS, infertility, and recurrent miscarriage, rather than masking symptoms or bypassing the body's natural function.
      </p>
      <p class="about-mission">Empower patients. Equip professionals. Restore women's health.</p>
      <p>
        As the primary educational project of the Restorative Reproductive Medicine Foundation, a 501(c)(3) non-profit, our focus is entirely on education for true healing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Is RRM -->
  <section class="about-section about-section--alt">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>What is Restorative Reproductive Medicine?</h2>
      <p>
        Restorative Reproductive Medicine (RRM) is an approach within conventional medicine that works cooperatively with the body to diagnose and treat the underlying causes of reproductive health conditions. Unlike approaches that mask symptoms with hormonal medications or bypass natural function with assisted reproductive technologies, RRM uses standard and advanced diagnostic tools to investigate the root cause, whether hormonal, anatomical, or inflammatory, and restore natural function.
      </p>
      <p>
        Conditions commonly addressed through RRM include endometriosis, polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS), unexplained infertility, recurrent pregnancy loss, irregular or painful menstrual cycles, hormonal imbalances, ovulatory dysfunction, and male factor infertility. For many patients, RRM offers an effective alternative by treating the underlying cause rather than bypassing it.
      </p>
      <a href="/faqs/what-is-restorative-reproductive-medicine-rrm/" class="about-learn-more">What is Restorative Reproductive Medicine? &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How RRM Academy Helps -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>How RRM Academy helps patients and professionals</h2>
      <p>
        RRM Academy bridges the gap between complex medical science and the people who need it most. We do this by:
      </p>
      <ul class="about-list">
        <li>
          <h3>Clinician-led online courses</h3>
          <p>Our courses are developed and taught by medical experts, translating years of clinical experience into accessible online education.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Patient education and empowerment</h3>
          <p>We equip individuals and couples with the knowledge to understand their bodies, ask informed questions, and advocate for better care.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Professional training and resources</h3>
          <p>We provide resources for healthcare providers who want to integrate restorative principles into their own practices.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Evidence-based research library</h3>
          <p>From in-depth masterclasses to our extensive research library, all of our content is grounded in scientific evidence and clinical best practices.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team -->
  <section class="about-section about-section--alt">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>Our team</h2>
      <p class="team-intro">
        RRM Academy is governed by the board of the Restorative Reproductive Medicine Foundation, the 501(c)(3) parent organization that funds and oversees its educational mission.
      </p>

      <div class="team-grid">
        {team.map((member) => <TeamCard member={member} />)}
      </div>

      <div class="team-follow">
        <p class="team-follow__label">Follow RRM Academy</p>
        <SocialRow size="md" variant="page" />
      </div>

      <aside class="about-clinical-note">
        <p>
          <strong>Looking to schedule with Dr Whittaker as a patient?</strong>
          <a href="/schedule-with-dr-whittaker/">See here for her clinical practice information</a>.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Support -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>Support our nonprofit mission</h2>
      <p>
        Whether you are a patient seeking answers about endometriosis, infertility, or hormonal health, a healthcare professional expanding your clinical skills, or a supporter who shares our vision, there are many ways to get involved:
      </p>
      <ul class="about-cta-list">
        <li>
          <a href="/courses/" class="about-cta-link">Explore our courses</a>
          <span>12 clinician-led online courses on topics from endometriosis surgery to understanding your fertility cycle</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/library/" class="about-cta-link">Browse the RRM Research Library</a>
          <span>{libraryCount} curated research publications, freely accessible</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/save-the-uterus-club/" class="about-cta-link">Join the Save the Uterus Club</a>
          <span>Support our 501(c)(3) nonprofit mission through monthly giving</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="about-ein">
        RRM Academy is a project of the Restorative Reproductive Medicine Foundation, a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization (EIN: 93-4594315).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .about-hero {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--gradient-hero-subtle);
  }
  .about-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .about-hero__tagline {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', 'Georgia', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  @media (min-width: 769px) {
    .about-hero__tagline {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }

  /* Sections — use global .page-body letter-line */
  .about-section {
    padding: 0;
  }
  .about-section--alt {
    background: none;
  }
  .about-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Lead paragraph — Body Large */
  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  /* Mission statement */
  .about-mission {
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* Feature list */
  .about-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  .about-list li {
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }
  .about-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .about-list h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .about-list p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Team section */
  .team-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .team-grid > :global(.team-card) {
      padding-block: var(--space-4);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    }
    .team-grid > :global(.team-card:last-child) {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
  }
  .team-follow {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    padding-top: var(--space-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .team-follow__label {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* Last-updated timestamp */
  .about-hero__updated {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .about-hero__updated time {
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* CTA list */
  .about-cta-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }
  .about-cta-list li {
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
  }
  .about-cta-list li:first-child {
    padding-top: 0;
  }
  .about-cta-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .about-cta-link {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .about-cta-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }
  .about-cta-list span {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* What is RRM learn-more link */
  .about-learn-more {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .about-learn-more:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* EIN — Caption size */
  .about-ein {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Clinical scheduling note */
  .about-clinical-note {
    margin: var(--space-10) auto 0;
    max-width: 36rem;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
  .about-clinical-note p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .about-clinical-note a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .about-clinical-note a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
